<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-20T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-20T15:00:00-05:00" n="280" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d280">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">816.24/620a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-20T16:00:00-04:00">July 20, 1943—4
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>150. The Coast Guard has been requested by the Salvadoran Military
                            Attaché to sell 1,000 surplus submachine guns to the Salvadoran
                            police.</p>
                        <p>Please ascertain very discreetly as much as you can concerning the
                            background and motives of this transaction and report by cable.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>